<HEADLINE>
GADZURIC OUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA freshman center Dan Gadzuric suffered a
potentially season-ending injury to his left knee Wednesday in
practice. Gadzuric had an MRI exam Wednesday night, and the results
are expected today. UCLA officials believe he may have torn the
meniscus cartilage in the knee. Gadzuric is doubtful for tonight's
game against Washington State and questionable for the remainder of
the season. Gadzuric is averaging 8.6 points and 5.7 rebounds per
game.
</P>
