<P>
   CRAFT-DESIGN (Undated) _ There are 13 million people in the
United States making crafts to sell, and over a billion dollars
being spent in the process. This could be construed as very bad
news. But it's not. Much of the most recent craft production is
more beautiful and more technically sophisticated than it has been
for 30 years _ since the heyday of American craft artists like
George Nakashima and Gertrude and Otto Natzler, the glittering era
of modern Italian art glass or the British studio pottery tradition
of and Lucie Rie. By William L. Hamilton.
</P>
