<HEADLINE>
STARS LOSE AS HULL TO MISS TWO WEEKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE HEIKA 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ The injury bug caught up with the Stars last night,
just as the Nashville Predators did.
</P>
<P>
   The Predators threw the Stars a changeup in a 2-1 Nashville
victory, and the injury bug claimed Brett Hull and Joe Nieuwendyk.
Hull is expected to be out ``a minimum of two weeks,'' Stars coach
Ken Hitchcock said, after Hull pulled a hamstring muscle when he
