A8590 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-STARS-NOTES-TEX     02-25 0314
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANKLE SPRAIN SIDELINES NIEUWENDYK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE HEIKA 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
DALLAS _ Stars center Joe Nieuwendyk missed last night's game with
a slight ankle sprain suffered the night before in Nashville,
Tenn. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nieuwendyk is listed as day-to-day. The 32-year-old center
missed five games at the beginning of the season and five games in
January because of residual pain from two knee operations in the
summer. Nieuwendyk is fifth on the Stars in scoring with 12 goals
and 20 assists for 32 points. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Last night, the Stars also were without Darryl Sydor (knee
injury, out two weeks) and Brian Skrudland (chest contusion, two to
four weeks) and lost Brett Hull to a leg injury in the third
period. Hull is expected to be re-evaluated today. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MCCREADY SINGS &QL; 
Country singing star Mindy McCready sang the national anthem last
night. She is the girlfriend of Predators player Drake Berehowsky. &QL; 
 &QL; 
SOLD OUT &QL; 
The Stars played host to their 24th consecutive sellout crowd of
16,928, extending their franchise record. The Stars have sold out
25 of 28 home games this season. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NICE TRIP &QL; 
The Stars and Predators had to travel from Nashville after
Tuesday's game for the home-and-home series. Due to the short
distance (Nashville is the Stars' closest geographical rival) and a
7 p.m. start on Tuesday, the Stars arrived back at Dallas/Fort
Worth Airport by 12:45 a.m. yesterday. It is the earliest the Stars
have returned from a road trip since moving to Texas in 1993. &QL; 
 &QL; 
THREE STARS &QL; 
1. Sergei Krivokrasov, Predators _ Amazing move to score game
winner &QL; 
2. Cliff Ronning, Predators _ A constant thorn in the Stars' side &QL; 
3. Tomas Vokoun, Predators _ Came up with big saves when needed &QL; 
 &QL; 
X-FACTOR &QL; 
The Stars seemed more tired from the back-to-back situation than
the Predators, who played a great road game. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
