<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKNOTE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UPSTAGED RODMAN EXPECTS TO DEBUT FRIDAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Picture this: After three weeks of grabbing
headlines just by !ital!thinking about joining the Lakers, Dennis
Rodman finally arrives at the Forum as a full-fledged member of the
purple and gold and he's not even the top news story of the day.
</P>
<P>
   It takes a lot to upstage Rodman, but the firing of coach Del
Harris did just that on an unusual Wednesday afternoon at the
Forum. The Lakers had originally scheduled a press briefing with
Rodman on the occasion of his first workout with the team after
signing a contract late Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   It was only once the media arrived that a Lakers spokesman noted
the team had ``made a coaching change.''
</P>
<P>
   But Rodman did take the podium after Harris, expressed sympathy
for the ousted coach and declared himself ready to play for the
newly reshuffled Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman signed a one-year deal for the veterans minimum salary _
$1 million, prorated to $463,414 for the remaining games _ and has
an option for a second year.
</P>
<P>
   The seven-time rebounding champion and noted cross-dresser said
he is in game shape but expected to make his playing debut Friday
night, when the Clippers come to the Forum. And he vowed to be the
same steady force here as he was while winning five NBA titles in
Chicago and Detroit.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's gonna be a lot of pressure on Dennis Rodman to produce
and bring some type of unity to this (team). But I get paid just
like everyone else on this team to go out there and work hard and
hopefully get us to the Finals,'' he said. ``I've been producing
for 12 years, and hopefully these guys see that and not be too
immature not to know that it's not all about fun and games, it's
all about winning basketball games here. It doesn't matter what
pressure I'm under, I always come through in the clutch.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman and team leader Shaquille O'Neal have verbally sparred in
the past, Rodman deriding O'Neal's game and O'Neal dismissing
Rodman as ``a bum.'' But O'Neal lobbied hard to bring the
``thuggish rebounder'' to the Lakers, and Rodman said they have put
all the harsh words behind them.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's no hard feelings,'' Rodman said. ``I've always
respected Shaq. We had a little choice words here and there about
each other.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman, who hid black-and-white hair under a large hat, said
Lakers management had made no demands of him with regard to his
appearance, his off-court behavior or other extracurricular
activities.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You're in the city of extracurricular,'' he said. ``This is
perfect for me, brother.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman went through a brief workout with Robert Horry and the
Lakers' three rookies while the rest of the team took a needed day
off.
</P>
<P>
   Horry said he'll happily play behind Rodman at power forward but
cautioned that Rodman's arrival guarantees nothing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dennis is not the answer. . . . Dennis is just a piece of the
puzzle we need,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Horry's return: Horry practiced for the first time since an
irregular heartbeat surfaced 12 days ago and said he felt fine.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everything is clear for me. I'm ready to go,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Doctors attributed the condition to a viral infection, but
Horry's heartbeat has returned to normal and the problem is not
expected to resurface. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
