<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Web offers clues, guesses, chat
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ There are a seemingly endless number of Web sites
devoted to ``Star Wars''' upcoming prequel, ``The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   Here's a quick rundown on some of the most popular (many include
links to other sites).
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.starwars.com _ Official ``Star Wars'' information
from Lucasfilm Ltd.
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.theforce.net _ Here's where you'll find what's
alleged to be a frame-by-frame description of the more than 103
film shots in the upcoming trailer.
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.thephantommenace.com _ Sometimes whimsical fan-run
site with everything from a Fandom Menace discussion about apparent
errors spotted in the first trailer to Aunt Beru's recipe for
Luke's Favorite Chocolate Chip Cookies.
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.countingdown.com _ Remarkable compilation of detail
from official announcements to spy reports (for example,
``Sheldon'' says he personally located the Sneak Preview
Battledroid/STAP toy set on sale in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, at the
Toys R Us in One Utama shopping center).
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.landspeeder.com _ Discussion board, chat rooms and
lots of rumors. Good pictures of new villain Darth Maul.
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.sirstevesguide.com _ Lots of toy information and
prequel characters lineup.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
