<SLUG> BC-BUTTER-POTERIE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BUTTER SPREADS EASILY WITH THE HELP OF THIS GADGET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   As kitchen gadgets go, the Butter Poterie is one of the better
ones. It's small, attractive and actually works.
</P>
<P>
   The poterie is a bell-shaped crock that you fill with butter and
invert into a matching container of water. The crock, which you can
leave on the kitchen counter, keeps butter at room temperature so
it's spreadable. The water seals the butter and prevents spoilage.
</P>
<P>
   But I don't want watery butter, you say. No problem. Butter is
fat and the water rolls off as if it were on a duck's back.
</P>
<P>
   The Butter Poterie comes in six designs, ranging in price from
$21.95 to $24.95. It is available by mail order from L. Tremain
Inc., Marina del Rey, Calif., at 888-575-1900.
</P>
</TEXT>
