(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob
McCarthy at (818) 713-3665. 
 
 
MAKING-8MM (Los Angeles) _ Nicolas Cage and director Joel
Schumacher took the more subdued approach making ``8mm,'' a film
about kiddie porn and violence that would turn most others away. By
Bob Strauss. 
 
 
8MM-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ Review of ``8mm.'' 2 stars. By Bob
Strauss. 
. 
ENCOUNTERS-REVIEW _ Review of the IMAX feature ``Encounters in the
Third Dimension.'' 3 stars. By David Bloom. 
. 
FLESH-REVIEW _ Review of ``School of Flesh.'' 3{ stars. By Bob
Strauss. 
. 
TICKET-REVIEW _ Review of ``Just the Ticket.'' 2 stars. By Glenn
Whipp. 
. 
WINDHORSE-REVIEW _ Review of ``Windhorse.'' 3 stars. By Bob
Strauss. 
. 
DATES-REVIEW _ Review of ``20 Dates.'' 3 stars. By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
CIGARETTES-REVIEW _ Review of ``200 Cigarettes.'' 1 star. By Glenn
Whipp. 
 
 
DISC-REVIEWS _ Reviews of new LPs.  
 
 
CHAIM-THEATER (Los Angeles) _ ``Chaim's Love Song'' made a gutsy
move to an off-Broadway venue after a 5-month local run and became
a rave success. By Reed Johnson. 
 
 
VIDEO-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ It's nice to see a grown-up Drew
Barrymore shine in ``Ever After: A Cinderella Story.'' By Rob
Lowman. 
 
 
SHARPS-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ A Keith Moon fan writes a bio of the
late wildman with the Who. By Fred Shuster. 
 
 
TOMMY-HENRIKSEN (Los Angeles) _ Tommy Henriksen has worked at a
copy store and roadied for Alice Cooper, and now he's waiting to
see what happens with his self-titled debut LP. By Fred Shuster. 

