<P>
   &QR;  Louisville, Ky. _ Humana Festival of New American Plays
showcases new theatrical works performed by the Actors Theatre of
Louisville. Through March 28. 502-584-1265.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Asheville, N.C. _ Liz Spear, a weaver, and Robert Stephan, a
glass artist, exhibit their latest work in the Folk Arts Center's
Focus Gallery today through March 24. 828-298-7928.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  DeFuniak Springs, Fla. _ Florida's Chautauqua Assembly '99
meets Friday through Feb. 28 with guest speakers including travel
photographers Ann and Carl Purcell, illustrator Lonnie Barringer,
actress Jan Turnquist (in ``The Surprising World of Louisa May
Alcott and Her Literary Friends'') and porcelain painter Mary
Vinson. In addition, a piano concert, Victorian tea, children's
theater, participatory arts and crafts and history lessons.
850-892-4300.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  St. Augustine, Fla. _ The third annual ``Flight to Freedom''
celebration Saturday at the Fort Mose Historic Site features
re-enactments of characters telling the story of the little-known
site where formerly enslaved Africans took refuge in Spanish
Florida in 1738. 904-461-2035.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lakeland. Fla. _ The Black Hills Passion Play opens March 11
in its new home at the Carpenter's Home Church Auditorium after 45
years in Lake Wales. The season will run 23 performances,
Thurdays-Sundays through Easter. Tickets $15 in advance or $17 at
the door; children 11 and under $8. 1-888-859-8877, Ext. 113, 117.
</P>
