   &QR;  Savannah, Ga. _ Savannah Onstage International Arts Festival
opens Saturday with a concert by Sweet Honey in the Rock at the
First African Baptist Church and ``Marni Nixon: The Voice of
Hollywood,'' an autobiographical theater piece with show music,
film clips and personal reminiscences, on Saturday. Concerts, music
competitions and ``offstage'' cultural events continue through
March 7. 1-800-868-3378 or http://www
</P>
<P>
   .savannahonstage.org
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Newport News, Va. _ ``Chris-Craft: The Affordable Dream'' will
be on display at the Mariner's Museum through Dec. 31. The exhibit
traces the American love affair with these mahogany boats while
giving visitors a taste of life in the 1920s and '30s.
1-800-581-7245.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Chattanooga _ The River Gallery in the Bluff View Art District
presents the Fourth Annual Russian Ukrainian Exhibition, featuring
paintings by contemporary Russian and Ukrainian artists. Opening
Monday; through March 31. Opening reception March 5. Also, dinner
to salute Russian and Ukrainian cuisine is March 5 (two seatings;
423-265-5033, Ext. 4). 1-800-374-2923.
