<P>
   COXNET-WHEELS-COX (Undated) _ North American buyers may not
immediately think of Audi when station wagons are mentioned, but
the European manufacturer actually has commonality with those
vehicles traditionally regarded as family haulers _ primarily,
change. Like the new-for-'99 A6 Avant, both Audi and station wagons
in general are putting the past far behind them. By Russ DeVault.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP DRIVING-COX (Undated) _ The most common perception of the
term platform is it means the vehicles share the same floor plan or
metal stamping that constitutes the ``floor'' of the car. That may
be the case on a shared-platform vehicle, but not necessarily. By
Linda Sharp.
