   &UR; NATIONAL-GENERAL  &LR;  (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DRAGGING-DEATH (Jasper, Texas) _ Jurors decided that John
William King should be executed for dragging a black man to his
death behind a pickup truck. By Rick Lyman.
</P>
<P>
   HOME-HEALTH-WORKERS (Los Angeles ) _ In the biggest single
unionization vote since workers at Ford's River Rouge plant joined
the UAW in 1941, 75,000 home-care workers are voting today on
whether to join the Service Employees International Union. The
organizing drive reflects labor's new emphasis on low wage,
minority workers. By Steven Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   CRUISESHIP-DUMPING (Undated) _ A federal grand jury in Los
Angeles has indicted Royal Caribbean for at-sea dumping from 1994.
By Douglas Frantz.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL  &LR;  (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-ADS (Undated) _ Traditional media companies in the
United States have long aspired to distinguish between paid
advertising and features created by producers or editors with no
objective other than to appeal to their audience. But on the
Internet, with bookstores becoming literary reviews and news
outlets turning into travel agents, it is hard to find a source of
information that does not have a financial stake in what its users
do with what the source publishes. Trusting an Internet site to
navigate the Web is like following a helpful stranger in Morocco
who offers to take you to the best rug store. You may well find
what you're looking for, but your guide will get a piece of
whatever you spend. By Saul Hansell and Amy Harmon.
</P>
