   CYC-ATLANTARACE _ ATLANTA _ For the first time in eight years,
professional cyclists will not race through the streets of Atlanta
this spring. The Atlanta Grand Prix is dead, or at least critically
wounded. The event fell victim to Atlanta city officials, who
wanted the race to be held in the autumn and would not grant a
spring permit, and to last year's sponsor, which did not want a
fall date. (ABrice, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
