<P>
   NASCAR 0225: Ford vs Chevy. It's a rivalry over which American
car maker makes the best, the baddest, the fastest set of wheels.
It's a rivalry with roots reaching to Jan. 26, 1906, when two
automobile pioneers _ Henry Ford and Louis Chevrolet _ appeared
together on the Daytona Beach shoreline to publicize their new
creations with races. Over the next nine decades, it evolved into a
rich slice of American pop culture. This layout includes a 4 col.
illustration of Chevy and Ford fanatics squaring off. (Capozzi,
Palm Beach Post)
</P>
