<P>
   UNDATED _ Progress can best be made by those not preoccupied
with planning the future. That's the counterintuitive message
delivered in a new book from first-time author Virginia Postrel,
who argues that dynamic growth in business and the economy is
possible only when individuals are free to experiment and react to
market forces instead of slavishly relying on blueprint models that
may not reflect the desires and demands of today's marketplace. By
TERESA McUSIC. Story has moved in ``f'' financial category. &QL; 
