Digitial employees than anticipated when it bought the company. By
Ronald Rosenberg. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   MALL-SALE (Boston) _ Taking advantage of a strong economy and
rapid consolidation in the mall industry, developer Stephen R. Karp
agrees to sell off a big chunk of his mall operations to the
nation's largest mall owner for $1.725 billion. By Chris Reidy. 800
words.
