<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Feb. 26. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
CLINTON-ARIZONA (Tucson, Ariz.) - President Clinton travels to
Arizona to visit with the Udall family, schmooze with snowbirds
over Social Security and hit a few with the boys of summer. By PAT
FLANNERY. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MEXFEE (Phoenix) - Mexico will start charging a $15 fee to enter
the interior of country on July 1. That will be at point 12 miles
south of Nogales and Agua Prieta and we're checking on Rocky Point.
By MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GAYKIDS (Gilbert, Ariz.) - Jesse Evans has had people spit on him,
hurl sexual slurs and throw trash at him. But he refuses to be
scared to admit he is gay. He and about 20 other students at
Gilbert High School formed the Gays, Lesbians and Straight
Supporters club earlier this year, much to the dismay of district
officials and even state lawmakers. It's believed to be the only
one of its kind in the Phoenix area. ``Things have been tense on
campus,'' said the 17-year-old senior, a red-ribbon pin on his
long-sleeved shirt. ``Gilbert is the last place you would expect
this club.'' We explore the pressures of being a teen-age
homosexual and why the club came to be. By KELLY PEARCE. Story
moved in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
EDIT-CLINTON (Phoenx) - - Dear Mr. President:
</P>
<P>
   Welcome to Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Enjoy your visit.
</P>
<P>
   No offense, sir, but don't you have more important things to do
than glad-hand with a large crowd of friendlies, including some of
those who helped put you over the top in Arizona during the last
presidential election? Story moved in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
