<P>
   LA-REFORM (Los Angeles) _ Reforming Los Angeles City Hall is
going to cost $7.4 million up front and anywhere from $4.9 million
to $19 million a year thereafter, according to a report released
Thursday. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTHY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Six-year-old Kelsy Boussard sold
500 boxes of Girl Scout cookies _ earning the Northridge Brownie a
place in cookie sales history at an overnight camp in Frasier Park.
Problem is: The Girl Scouts don't allow Brownies at the camp,
fearing they are too yougn for the overnight experience. By Dennis
McCarthy. (Will move in the ``k'' op-ed news file.)
</P>
<P>
   GM-DEALERS (Los Angeles) _ Developments in the ongoing dispute
between General Motors Corp. and some of its dealers in the Los
Angeles area, the nation's largest car buying market. By Gregory J.
Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   VIACOM-FORECAST (Los Angeles) _ Sumner Redstone, chief of Viacom
Inc., predicts that his company can post better profit growth than
any other media company in the world. Viacom posted a
larger-than-expected fourth-quarter profit due to strong
performance at MTV, Nickelodeon, ``The Rugrats Movie'' and
Blockbuster. By Dave McNary.
</P>
