</P>
<P>
   FILM-8MM (Undated) _ Joel Schumacher's new mystery-thriller,
``Eight Millimeter,'' could well have the distinction of being the
most thoroughly sordid and depressing Hollywood big-studio film of
the '90s. It gives a whole new meaning to the word ``downer.'' It's
numbingly vacuous at its core, and _ despite its sanctimonious tone
and ``serious'' subject matter _ it's basically an exploitation
film that's out to shock, titillate and appeal to the absolute
worst in its audience.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
