<P>
   FILM-SISTER (Undated) _ ``The Other Sister'' is no masterpiece
and definitely has its share of wincing moments, but it's an
incorrigibly sweet-spirited affair that gradually finds a pleasing
middle ground between an affliction-of-the-week weepie and a
rollicking domestic comedy.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-ALICE (Undated) _ There's precious little of Lewis Carroll's
nonsense language in NBC's latest version of ``Alice in
Wonderland,'' and several familiar characters are also missing.
Nonetheless, it is a lavish, loving tribute, and if it sends many
kids and their parents in search of the unabridged version, the
Cheshire Cat's grin will last a long, long time.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-HUSKIES (Los Angeles) _ University of Washington plays at
the University of Southern California.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Moore. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Seattle) _ On SuperSonic Vin Baker's
offseason. What did he do to deserve this?
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
