<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Fulmer, Williams to be honored
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Tennessee coach Phillip Fulmer and Grambling coach
Doug Williams will be among the honorees at a pair of college
football award banquets in Atlanta this weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Fulmer, who led the Volunteers to the national title last
season, will be honored by the Atlanta Touchdown Club Saturday as
its SEC and national coach of the year. Other coaches recognized
during the 61st annual awards banquet at the Cobb Galleria Centre
include Georgia Tech's George O'Leary, as ACC coach of the year,
and Georgia Southern's Paul Johnson, Division I-AA coach of the
year.
</P>
<P>
   Others scheduled to appear include Kentucky quarterback Tim
Couch, Tennessee linebacker Al Wilson, Georgia Tech center Craig
Page and Florida defensive back Teako Brown.
</P>
<P>
   Williams will be honored Saturday as the Sheridan Broadcast
Network holds its 25th annual All-American Awards banquet at the
Hyatt Regency in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, the former Grambling quarterback who replaced coach
Eddie Robinson at his alma mater before last season, will be
recognized as one of several former standouts on the SBN all-time
team from historically black colleges.
</P>
<P>
   Other black-college performers that will be honored at the
Sheridan event include Florida A&AMP;M quarterback Pat Bonner,
offensive player of the year; Mississippi Valley State linebacker
Terry Houzah, defensive player of the year; and Bethune-Cookman's
Alvin Wyatt, coach of the year.
</P>
