elevate it to reaching a higher good in terms of improving the
quality of people's lives,'' he says. (Michelle V. Agins/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) CALCUTTA, India -- Feb. 25, 1999 -- CALCUTTA-SUBWAYS-2,
2-25 -- Riders on a subway earlier this week. When someone in the
city wants to be in a clean and safe place, where politeness is
considered important and the beggars, the ornery and the
drug-addicted are absent, they can go to the subway. The city's
name has historically conjured up images of wretched filth, teeming
streets and insidious disease. But Calcutta's subway, now 14 years
old, has come to be regarded as a buried treasure. (Barry
Bearak/New York Times Photo)
</P>
