   ENCRYPT _ San Jose Rep. Zoe Lofgren will reintroduce bipartisan
legislation in Congress on Thursday that would loosen export
controls on encryption software, a major priority for Silicon
Valley high-tech businesses. The Security and Freedom through
Encryption Act would allow for a onetime review of most encryption
software and other products by the Commerce Department before sales
would be allowed outside the country. By Benny Evangelista
