saying it would not set manufacturers suggested retail prices. That
agreement expired a few months ago. Because of a relaxation of
antitrust laws over the past two years, Levi's can and is
reintroducing suggested prices and threatening retailers with
retaliation if they don't comply. Among other things, they are
threatening to withhold shipments and cutback back on advertising
money. By Carol Emert
