<P>
   SCI-ANTIBIOTICS (Undated) _ Bacteria resistant to antibiotics
have been found in food for poultry, and scientists are concerned
that this poses an eventual risk to humans. By Denise Grady.
</P>
<P>
   DUNE-BUGGY-CAPITAL (Glamis, Calif.) _ Alan Hamada chuckled as a
bucket's worth of sand landed in his face. He laughed harder when
another load hit him, pouring onto his lap and seeping into his
jeans, socks and high-tops. ``Ha,'' he said, ``I got used to that a
long time ago.'' Very little can get in the way of Hamada's good
time when he rides his dune buggy on the undulating sands of the
California desert. Officially, his playpen, which is overseen by
the Bureau of Land Management, is known as the Imperial San Dunes
Recreation Area. But to most people who come here, the 125,000
acres of dunes that they joy ride in is simply ``Glamis,'' the
sand-toy capital of the world. By Evelyn Nieves.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos [NYT27,28 have been sent to NYT photo clients.
Locator map has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
