<P>
   EPIDEMIC-EXHIBIT (New York) _ There's something about deadly
epidemics that both terrifies and fascinates people. One of the
best attended exhibitions ever mounted by the New York's American
Museum of Natural History was a six-week show in 1908. After a long
absence, germs are back at the museum. This weekend a new
exhibition will open in which dozens of infectious-disease
organisms will strut their stuff as computer animations,
eye-catching models, microphotographs, dioramas, and even real (but
dead) disease microorganisms. It is called ``Epidemic! The World of
Infectious Disease,'' and in this viewer's estimation, it is the
most impressive and informative exhibition the museum has mounted
in years. By Malcolm W. Browne.
